HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 990
By Hawk
A RESOLUTION to honor the life and legacy of David Crockett
and to commemorate March 2-6, 2026, as "Bring
David Crockett Home Week" in Tennessee.
WHEREAS, David Crockett was a renowned frontiersman, soldier, statesman, and folk
hero whose life and legacy are deeply intertwined with the history and the identity of the State of
Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, born in Greene County, David Crockett rose from humble beginnings to
serve his fellow Tennesseans in the Tennessee General Assembly and the United States
Congress, where he became known for his independent spirit and commitment to public service;
and
WHEREAS, throughout his life, David Crockett lived, worked, and served in communities
across East, Middle, and West Tennessee, including Greene County, where he was born;
Franklin and Lawrence counties, where he established himself as a hunter, businessman, and
local leader; Gibson County, where he later lived and served the people of West Tennessee in
the U.S. Congress; and Nashville, where he served in the Tennessee General Assembly,
representing Lawrence and Hickman counties; and
WHEREAS, David Crockett had ties to multiple regions of the State, a reflection of the
breadth of his influence and the lasting presence of his legacy in historic sites and communities
across Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, David Crockett's life exemplified the values of courage, perseverance, and
frontier ingenuity that continue to define Tennessee's character and heritage, and his enduring
influence is reflected in the creation of Crockett County by the Tennessee General Assembly,
with its county seat of Alamo named in his honor, and
