- 1 -

WHEREAS, the David Crockett Birthplace State Park preserves the site of his birth and
serves as a lasting tribute to his life and legacy, offering Tennesseans and visitors the
opportunity to experience and learn about one of the State's most iconic historical figures; and
WHEREAS, the preservation, interpretation, and continued restoration of David Crockett
Birthplace State Park are essential to protecting Tennessee's historic resources and ensuring
that future generations can connect with the State's early history; and
WHEREAS, honoring David Crockett through education, preservation, and stewardship
of his birthplace not only preserves his Tennessee roots but also strengthens public
understanding of his life beyond legend, grounding his story in the place, people, and values
that shaped him; and
WHEREAS, David Crockett's life came to an end on March 6, 1836, at the Battle of the
Alamo, where he made the ultimate sacrifice; this anniversary serves as a solemn moment of
reflection on his courage and enduring impact on American history; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we commemorate the week of March 2-6, 2026, as "Bring David Crockett
Home Week," as Tennesseans from all walks of life learn about, reflect upon, honor, and
support the preservation of David Crockett's life, legacy, and historic birthplace.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
